// Adversarial: Once([Do(DamageBoost(3.0))]) is nested inside When(Impacted(Cell)) so it fires
// on the very first cell impact. The Once node must be consumed and must never re-arm.
// Dense layout under Perfect tracking drives hundreds of cell impacts across 5000 frames — if
// Once re-fires on subsequent impacts, DamageBoost(3.0) stacks permanently and the multiplier
// diverges. A corrupted ActiveSpeedBoosts calculation from runaway DamageBoost stacks
// can flow back into speed state. Godmode breaker ensures infinite play to maximise
// re-trigger opportunities. NoEntityLeaks catches leaked OnceConsumed or sentinel entities
// left behind by the Once bookkeeping system. NoNaN catches any f32 overflow from an
// unbounded stacking multiplier. BoltSpeedAccurate is a secondary signal that speed-boosting
// side effects of damage overflow are caught at the physics boundary.
(
    breaker: "godmode",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Perfect(AlwaysPerfect),
    max_frames: 5000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltSpeedAccurate, NoEntityLeaks, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 1337,
    initial_effects: [
        On(target: AllBolts, then: [
            When(trigger: Impacted(Cell), then: [
                Once([
                    Do(DamageBoost(3.0)),
                ]),
            ]),
        ]),
    ],
)
